HEADWORD: Peirameter
<hw>Pei*ram"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pei^ra</grk> a trial + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>A dynamometer
for measuring the force required to draw wheel carriages on roads of
different constructions.</def> <rj><au>G. Francis.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

